HEADWORD: ethnocentrism
<hw>ethnocentrism</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>belief in the
superiority of one's own ethnic group.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a tendency to evaluate other people, activities,
cultures, etc. primarily from the perspective of one's own as being
superior.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ethnographer</ent>⟦br⟧
